node.text:
HUGE BUG in man’s lip! 🐛 
.
This video shows the larvae of a botfly being removed from the upper lip of a man’s mouth! 
.
The botfly (mainly located in South America) is one of the few species who incubates it’s larvae on humans. 🤢
.
When this happens, a botfly latches onto a mosquito and attaches their eggs to the mosquitoes stomach. 
Then, when the mosquito lands on a human's skin, the botfly eggs burrow into the tiny wound of the mosquito bite, and the eggs then turn into larvae. 
.
If not removed like in this video, the larvae will fully grow and then dig their way out from underneath the person’s skin and fly away.

node.text:
17 pound baby! 👶 Can you imagine giving birth to a baby this size?!

Incredibly, this baby was born by natural vaginal birth, weighing roughly 17.47 pounds (7.9 kg) and 22.5 inches (57.5 cm) long!
.
The heaviest baby ever born, according to the Guinness Book of World Records, was born in 1955 in Italy, and weighed a whopping 22 pounds and 8 ounces (10.2kg) when he was delivered.
.
Coming in at a close second, was a baby born in the state of Ohio in 1879 who weighed 22 pounds (10kg) and was nearly 30 inches long (75 cm); each of his feet was said to be six inches (152 mm) long!

Photo credit: @medicalpedia @doktorcuneytuzun 
#obstetrics #baby #childbirth #emergencymedicine #hospital #nurse #doctor #deliveryroom #guinnessworldrecord #medical

node.text:
81 teeth in one mouth! 🦷 
This is a very rare case of extreme hyperdontia. 
Hyperdontia is the condition of having extra teeth that appear in addition to the regular number of teeth (32 in the average adult). The extra teeth can appear in any area of the dental arch. 
.
These X-ray images show a patient with a total of 81 teeth: 18 deciduous, 32 permanent, and 31 supernumerary. 
.
Treatment for Hyperdontia often includes surgical removal of the extra teeth and orthodontic treatment. Orthodontic treatment is usually indicated to direct the eruption of the impacted teeth. 
.
The treatment of this patient, however, is a challenge. With so many extra teeth, dental extractions had to be carefully done as not to jeopardize the osseous integrity of the maxilla and the mandible.
.
In most cases of Hyperdontia, the patient only has a small number of extra teeth (not the extreme number seen in these photos). The extra teeth may need to be removed to prevent crowding. In other cases, extra teeth may be left alone and observed over time if they're not causing any problems.

Globe rupture and iris herniation!👁

This eye injury was caused during a fight and a punch to the eye. 
Luckily the patient was taken to the hospital and underwent surgery for globe repair by an ophthalmologist. He recovered with no vision loss.
